               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18290611-368-off1924-c1956" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290611-368-defend2555 t18290611-368-off1924 t18290611-368-verdict1928"></join>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18290611-368-off1924-c1957" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290611-368-defend2557 t18290611-368-off1924 t18290611-368-verdict1930"></join>
         
               <p>NEW COURT, Eighth Day.</p>
               <p>Second London Jury. - Before Mr. Common Sergeant.</p>
               <p>1365. 
               
                  <persName id="t18290611-368-defend2555" type="defendantName">
                     HENRY 
                     LIGHTFORD
                  <interp inst="t18290611-368-defend2555" type="surname" value="LIGHTFORD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-defend2555" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-defend2555" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-defend2555" type="age" value="25"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             and 
               
                  <persName id="t18290611-368-defend2557" type="defendantName">
                     THOMAS 
                     WILSON
                  <interp inst="t18290611-368-defend2557" type="surname" value="WILSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-defend2557" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-defend2557" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             were indicted for <rs id="t18290611-368-off1924" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-off1924" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-off1924" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18290611-368-cd1925" type="crimeDate">18th of May</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290611-368-off1924 t18290611-368-cd1925"></join>, 1 diamond pin, value 30s., the goods of 
                     <persName id="t18290611-368-victim2558" type="victimName">
                        Thomas 
                        Wick
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-victim2558" type="surname" value="Wick"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18290611-368-victim2558" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18290611-368-victim2558" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290611-368-off1924 t18290611-368-victim2558"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290611-368-person2559">
                  THOMAS 
                  WICK
               <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2559" type="surname" value="WICK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2559" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2559" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an <rs id="t18290611-368-viclabel1926" type="occupation">auctioneer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290611-368-victim2558 t18290611-368-viclabel1926"></join>, and live in West Smithfield. On the 18th of May, between twelve and one o'clock in the night, I was on <placeName id="t18290611-368-crimeloc1927">Snow-hill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18290611-368-crimeloc1927" type="placeName" value="Snow-hill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290611-368-crimeloc1927" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290611-368-off1924 t18290611-368-crimeloc1927"></join>, with a lady - a female was behind me; I saw several persons, and the two prisoners were among them; the prisoners were together, and were at first behind me - they then came in front of me; Lightford shoved up against me - I asked what he did it for: he made no remark, but took the pin out of my breast with his thumb and finger; he went a little way back - I said to him, "You have got my pin - give it me, and go along about your business:" he said, "I have not got your pin;" in the mean time Wilson struck my female servant, who was behind - she called out Watch! and I held Lightford till the watchman came and took him: I do not know what became of the pin - it has not been found- the other persons were further up the bill; after I gave Lightford in charge, Wilson came up and struck me - I think he was two or three yards off when Lightford took the pin.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PRENDERGAST. Q. Do you mean that you gave Wilson in charge? A.Certainly I did, for striking me, and he struck 
               <persName id="t18290611-368-person2560">
                  Catherine 
                  Conner
               <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2560" type="surname" value="Conner"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2560" type="given" value="Catherine"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2560" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , who was with her husband, behind me; there were four of us together - 
               <persName id="t18290611-368-person2561">
                  Sophia 
                  Aaron
               <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2561" type="surname" value="Aaron"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2561" type="given" value="Sophia"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2561" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was with me: a minute or two elapsed after I lost the pin, before Conner complained at Wilson striking her; we had no thought of taking him till he came and struck me - I saw them together, and three others with them.</p>
               <p>COURT. Q. Do you think Wilson saw Lightford take the pin? A. His back was towards him, he might not possibly.</p>
               <p>SOPHIA AARON. I was with Mr. Wick on Snow-hill. I saw Lightford take the pin from his breast - Wilson was about a yard from him at the time; I do not know whether he saw what Lightford did: Conner gave an alarm when Wilson struck her.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Did you see what he did? A. He passed us to strike her - I turned round.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290611-368-person2562">
                  CATHERINE 
                  CONNER
               <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2562" type="surname" value="CONNER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2562" type="given" value="CATHERINE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2562" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was behind the witnesses - I did not see the pin taken; I saw Lightford near the pro<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182906110161"></xptr>secutor - Wilson then came and struck me, and I called Watch!</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290611-368-person2563">
                  EDWARD 
                  BARTRUM
               <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2563" type="surname" value="BARTRUM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2563" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2563" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a tin-plate-worker. On the morning of the 19th of May I was on Snow-hill - I saw Lightford and several others in company; he went up and assaulted the prosecutor - I heard him say, "I have lost my pin;" Lightford said, "I have not got it;" Wick said,"Give it me, and go along about your business;" he collared him, and called the watch - Wilson was by his side, rather behind him; I do not suppose he could see what Lightford did.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Had you seen Wilson with him before? A. Yes - they were sober, to my knowledge.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290611-368-person2564">
                  JOSEPH 
                  RICE
               <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2564" type="surname" value="RICE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2564" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2564" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. I took Lightford; in the way to the watch-house Wilson and two or three others attacked the prosecutor - I sprung my rattle; another watchman came and took Wilson - I will not swear that Wilson was sober.</p>
               <p>MR. PRENDERGAST to 
               <persName id="t18290611-368-person2565">
                  CATHERINE 
                  CONNER
               <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2565" type="surname" value="CONNER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2565" type="given" value="CATHERINE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2565" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Q. Were not you struck first? A. Yes - there were five or six of them together; the watchman came to Mr. Wick before he came to me - the pin was taken before I was struck at all.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290611-368-person2566">
                  JOHN 
                  DELL
               <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2566" type="surname" value="DELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2566" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-person2566" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I received the prisoners at the watch-house; Wilson was the most sober - Lightford had been drinking.</p>
               <p>LIGHTFORD'S Defence. I was walking down Snow-hill, and happened to run against one of the women - the prosecutor and I had some words; I was a little inebriated, and challenged him to fight - I certainly did hit him in the breast, and he called the watchman, and gave charge of me for stealing the pin.</p>
               <p>WILSON'S Defence. I was going home from my trademeeting that night - I saw a mob, and went up; I was tipsy, and do not know whether I struck any body or not; I went voluntarily to the watch-house.</p>
               <p>JURY to MR. WICK. Q. Was it near a lamp you lost your pin? A. Yes - I saw it very plainly in his hand, between his thumb and finger.</p>
               <p>LIGHTFORD - <rs id="t18290611-368-verdict1928" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-verdict1928" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 25.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18290611-368-punish1929" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-punish1929" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290611-368-defend2555 t18290611-368-punish1929"></join>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290611-368-defend2557 t18290611-368-punish1929"></join>
               Transported for Life
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>WILSON - <rs id="t18290611-368-verdict1930" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290611-368-verdict1930" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               NOT GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
